Vendored ExprTk expression evaluator
=====================================

Source repo : ~/Code/PyBNF-Private/bngsim  (BNGsim)
Pinned commit: f5cbc33c42f9c84ade79287cb80da44c908e1406
               ("fix(bngsim): mangle bngsim-only function aliases to match
                 BNGL contract", 2026-05-10)

Vendored files (copied verbatim, no edits):
  third_party/exprtk/exprtk.hpp                       <- bngsim third_party/exprtk/exprtk.hpp
  third_party/bngsim_expr/include/bngsim/expression.hpp <- bngsim include/bngsim/expression.hpp
  third_party/bngsim_expr/src/expression.cpp          <- bngsim src/expression.cpp

Why these are here
------------------
RuleMonkey's rate-law / function expression evaluator is bngsim::ExprTkEvaluator
(see issue #6, dev/exprtk_swap_plan_2026_05_16.md). RM is itself vendored into
BNGsim, which ALREADY ships these exact files. To avoid compiling two copies of
the bngsim:: symbols into a single binary:

  * CMakeLists.txt gates the vendored copy on `if(TARGET bngsim::expression)`:
    inside a BNGsim build RM links the host's target; standalone RM builds
    compile this vendored copy.
  * BNGsim's scripts/vendor_rulemonkey.py MUST exclude third_party/exprtk/ and
    third_party/bngsim_expr/ from the RM copy it pulls in (action item tracked
    in the swap plan §4.3a).

Updating
--------
Re-copy all three files together from the same BNGsim commit and update the
pin above. exprtk.hpp is header-only — two identical copies merge fine, but
version skew between RM's copy and BNGsim's is undefined behavior.
